{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"0679ce59c59e006e22b8a099a98494c5","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Got it. Now I have full picture:\n\nF-201 MandatoEsqueleto shape:\n- `pilares_relevantes: string[]` (P1-P5)\n- `redacao_bruta: string` (text w/ escala + pilares + vida + LLM hint)\n- `cita_fontes: string[]` (fontes citadas)\n- Mentor hook: `{intencao, crise_detectada, recurso}`\n\nF-202 task: rewrite `/diario/page.tsx` to consume F-201's MandatoEsqueleto, show:\n- 3 frases (parsed from redacao_bruta or use as-is)\n- 1 pergunta (extract or display)\n- 1 micro-ritual\n- Cita fontes\n- CVV-188 recurso se crise_detectada\n\nExisting page consumes `/api/akasha/daily` (old shape). F-202 = migrate to `/api/akasha/mandato-do-dia`.\n\nLet me look at the diario page structure and design new one with the Mandato data. Keep the 3-screen format (Clima/Desafio/Prescrição) but with new data.\n\nPlan for F-202:\n1. Replace fetch from `/api/akasha/daily` to `/api/akasha/mandato-do-dia`\n2. Adapt types to MandatoEsqueleto + mentor_hook\n3. Display redacao_bruta as the \"3 frases\" (parse on `\\n` or just show as paragraphs)\n4. Extract pergunta + micro-ritual from redacao_bruta or treat as additional\n5. Show pilares_relevantes as badges\n6. Show cita_fontes as small citations\n7. If mentor_hook.crise_detectada → show CVV-188 card (not redacao_bruta)\n8. Add `intencao` query param to share with the user\n\nMandato is \"1 push/dia 06h, 3 frases + 1 pergunta + 1 micro-ritual\" per VISION.md §4. The redacao_bruta from R-030 currently is concatenated text. We can either:\n- Display as-is (acceptable v1, the LLM hint says \"3 frases + 1 pergunta + 1 micro-ritual\" goes in redacao)\n- Parse the LLM redacao when available (but R-030 has no LLM yet, so redacao_bruta is the placeholder)\n\nFor F-202 the practical solution: parse `redacao_bruta` by splitting on `.|?|\\n` to extract frases. Show pilares_relevantes + cita_fontes as meta. Add a clear note \"Módulo LLM será integrado em F-204\".\n\nLet me design the new page:\n\n```tsx\ntype MandatoEsqueleto = {\n  pilares_relevantes: string[];\n  redacao_bruta: string;\n  cita_fontes: string[];\n};\ntype MentorHook = {\n  intencao: string;\n  crise_detectada: boolean;\n  recurso: string | null; // 'CVV-188'\n};\ntype ApiResponse = {\n  date: string;\n  mandato: MandatoEsqueleto;\n  mentor_hook: MentorHook;\n};\n```\n\nScreen 1 - Mandato (3 frases):\n- Saudação data + intent\n- Pilares relevantes badges\n- Frases (split redacao_bruta into sentences)\n- Cita fontes as small footer\n\nScreen 2 - Pergunta (1 pergunta):\n- Extract pergunta from redacao_bruta (last sentence ending with ?)\n- Or default: \"O que seu Ori te pede hoje?\"\n\nScreen 3 - Micro-ritual:\n- Extract from redacao_bruta (the part with \"ritual\" or default)\n- Pilar X + ritual\n\nCrisis mode (mentor_hook.crise_detectada):\n- Don't render redacao_bruta\n- Show CVV-188 card prominently\n\nLet me write the new page. Be caveman — terse, surgical. Use existing styles.\n\nLook at F-201 response shape more carefully and the existing page already has good styling I should reuse.\n\nLet me also check what the page redirects to: `/onboarding` on 401/404. Same for the new API.\n\nAuth check: F-201 has 401 (no session), 404 (no Mapa natal), 400 (dados incompletos).\n\nLet me write F-202 now. Surgical change: swap fetch + types + render. Keep styling.\n\nRead F-201 test for response shape:","signature":"767454847380fe39f7c1216a377d438739bf037fa43e36311a147c370eea50a4"}],"model":"MiniMax-M3","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"service_tier":"standard"},"service_tier":"standard","context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d38a58d5-31a6-4161-80e1-d8d9df0b821e","uuid":"af172590-3047-43d8-9294-c07d76629a4e"}
