{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"0679ce7d4d0ae02c1169c71d2612f37b","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Got it. `pilares_relevantes` uses keys: `cabala`, `astrologia`, `tantrica`, `odu`, `iching`. `escala` is `D|S|Z|V`. `redacao_bruta` is the LLM placeholder text.\n\nNow I have full context. Let me also check the existing MandalaAtmosphere import and structure to keep style consistent. Then write F-202 — replace the diario page to consume the new F-201 endpoint with MandatoEsqueleto shape.\n\nPlan:\n- Keep 3-screen layout but adapt to Mandato data\n- Screen 1 = Mandato (3 frases + pilares + cita_fontes)\n- Screen 2 = A Pergunta do Dia (extract or default)\n- Screen 3 = O Micro-Ritual (extract or default + pilar)\n- Crisis mode: if mentor_hook.crise_detectada, replace Screen 1 with CVV-188 card and skip content\n\nCode-wise, since the redacao_bruta in R-030 is just placeholder text, the page should:\n- Show redacao_bruta as the main Mandato text (the \"3 frases\")\n- The \"1 pergunta\" and \"1 micro-ritual\" are stub fields in R-030 (not in MandatoEsqueleto yet). I should add a follow-up note that LLM integration will populate them. OR: extract a pergunta heuristically (last ? sentence) and show a default micro-ritual.\n\nFor F-202 v1 (surgical), display:\n- The 3 frases from redacao_bruta (split on `.` boundaries)\n- Pilares as badges\n- Fontes as small footer\n- A pergunta placeholder (\"A pergunta do dia virá quando o LLM for integrado em F-204\")\n- A micro-ritual placeholder (\"O micro-ritual do dia virá quando o LLM for integrado em F-204\")\n\nActually better: I'll show redacao_bruta as 1 paragraph, then add 2 fixed text cards (pergunta + ritual) that explain what they ARE per VISION spec — even if the LLM text isn't there yet. This way the user sees the structure of \"Mandato = 3 frases + 1 pergunta + 1 ritual\" even if the dynamic content is coming.\n\nBetter still: I can have the page render `redacao_bruta` AND a deterministic pergunta (last `?` sentence) AND a default micro-ritual that names a Pilar. This is more honest.\n\nLet me check what info the diario page can get from the API to derive pergunta/ritual. Looking at redacao_bruta: it ends with \"(LLM redige 3 frases + 1 pergunta + 1 micro-ritual.)\". So in v1 there's no real pergunta/ritual.\n\nSimpler approach: show 3 screens as promised by VISION, with what's actually available. Don't fake. Mark the LLM-dependent fields as \"em breve\" with a clear \"Stub\" badge OR show a fixed template.\n\nI'll go with: \n- Screen 1: redacao_bruta split by `.` into 3 sentences (best effort, fallback if no splits)\n- Screen 2: \"A Pergunta do Dia\" — use heuristic: last sentence ending in `?`, else default \"O que seu Ori pede a você hoje?\" with note that LLM customization comes in F-204\n- Screen 3: \"O Micro-Ritual\" — fixed: \"Reserve 3 min para [pilar X] (ex: oração ao orixá, respiração, escrita livre)\" with note\n\nOr even simpler: just show the redacao_bruta as 1 paragraph in screen 1, and screens 2-3 are \"O que virá\" placeholders that show VISION promises.\n\nActually the cleanest F-202 is: **make the page work end-to-end with the new API**. The Mandato is a single redacao_bruta for now. The \"pergunta\" and \"ritual\" are future LLM. So the page should:\n- Show redacao_bruta as the Mandato (3 frases if possible)\n- Have a section that says \"A pergunta do dia será escrita pelo LLM (F-204)\" \n- Have a section that says \"O micro-ritual do dia será escrito pelo LLM (F-204)\"\n- Use pilares_relevantes + cita_fontes to show provenance\n\nFor UX, let me show 3 screens but only #1 has real data, #2 and #3 show the LLM-dependent fields with a clear \"via LLM (F-204)\" badge.\n\nLet me write this. I'll keep the existing styles and just replace the data layer + types.\n\nGoing to do a surgical replacement: same file, same 3-screen structure, new data.\n\nLet me write it.","signature":"996248a42fc2a1d86f3800d211955c6245d24ceaf986